name: Greek Easter
summary: In celebration of Orthodox Easter, various news articles delve into the traditions and significance of this religious holiday. Red eggs symbolize renewal and are traditionally dyed and exchanged during the celebration, as explained in The Greek Herald's article. The different dates for Orthodox and Catholic Easter are discussed in Hope 103.2's report, highlighting the use of the Julian calendar in the Orthodox tradition. Greek Easter is also highlighted in JOY 94.9's article, emphasizing the cultural aspects and dance performances associated with the holiday. In Melbourne, Australia, Queen Victoria Market prepares for the influx of shoppers during Orthodox Easter, according to Neos Kosmos. The conflict in Ukraine has prompted Catholic leaders to advocate for a prisoner swap during Orthodox Easter, as reported by The Pillar. FOX 17 explores the unique practices of Orthodox Easter, while GreekCityTimes provides details about transportation schedules in Athens during the holiday period. Additionally, Aleteia reports on the Ukrainian leader's call for a prisoner exchange over Orthodox Easter, and the Victoria Advocate announces the date for Orthodox Easter as May 5th.

name: Ostarine
summary: Boxer Ryan Garcia has tested positive for a banned substance known as ostarine. Sources claim that the substance was found in Garcia's system both before and after his fight with Devin Haney. Ostarine is a performance-enhancing drug (PED) that is commonly used by athletes to increase muscle mass and strength. Garcia has denied using the substance and has stated that he will be taking legal action against those who have accused him of cheating. The news of Garcia's failed drug test has shocked the boxing world and has raised questions about the integrity of the sport.
